"{\"uid\": \"aljazeera.com-gallery-2024-8-12-photos-tom-cruise-hands-olympic-flag-to-los-angeles-closing-paris-games\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"In Pictures  Paris has closed out two and a half extraordinary weeks of Olympic sports with a star-studded show.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 112, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999902229, \"rank\": 9.801298747753404e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Save  Share  Hollywood actor Tom Cruise abseiled from the roof of the Stade de France as Paris saidfarewell to an Olympic Gameshailed as one of the most successful.\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 127, \"end\": 136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998223611486, \"rank\": 1.7763872534250638e-07, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 143, \"end\": 153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}, {\"begin\": 203, \"end\": 208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999902229, \"rank\": 9.801298747753404e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cruise descended on a wire in front of 71,500 spectators on Sunday evening, grabbed the Olympic flag and jumped on a motorbike, to the delight of athletes and fans.\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 444, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a preview of what the world can expect when the games head to Los Angeles in 2028, the \\\"Mission Impossible\\\" star was then shown boarding a plane and skydiving into the Californian city before adorning the iconic Hollywood sign with the Olympic rings.\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999581632, \"rank\": 3.041638743157527e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 661, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles band Red Hot Chili Peppers, singer Billie Eilish and rappers Snoop Dogg and Dr Dre then performed a mini-concert on a beach framed by the azure waters of the Pacific Ocean.\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 701, \"end\": 712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999581632, \"rank\": 3.041638743157527e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 718, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Red Hot Chili Peppers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\"}, {\"begin\": 748, \"end\": 761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Billie Eilish\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\"}, {\"begin\": 774, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dr._Dre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dr Dre\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dr._Dre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dr._Dre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The closing spectaclemarked the beginning of the four-year countdown to the LA Games.\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 972, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"US gymnastics icon Simone Biles joined Los Angeles Mayor Karen Bass as the Olympic flag was formally handed over.\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 973, \"end\": 975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_200\", \"score\": 0.5590718368827534, \"rank\": 0.6488359860236116, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_200\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billboard_200\"}, {\"begin\": 992, \"end\": 1004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 1012, \"end\": 1023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999581632, \"rank\": 3.041638743157527e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 1030, \"end\": 1040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Bass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier, International Olympic Committee (IOC) President Thomas Bach said the Paris Games had been \\\"sport at its best\\\".\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1207, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These were sensational Olympic Games from start to finish,\\\" Bach said.\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1270, \"end\": 1274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.33517683469203e-13, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Or dare I say: Seine-sational Games,\\\" the IOC chief quipped in a pun about the river flowing through Paris which was the scene of the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1433, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1324, \"end\": 1327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.398442027575894e-20, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1383, \"end\": 1388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999902229, \"rank\": 9.801298747753404e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Dear French friends, you have fallen in love with the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1504, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And we have fallen in love with all of you,\\\" Bach added.\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1550, \"end\": 1554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.33517683469203e-13, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"About 9,000 athletes had flooded into the stadium to be entertained by 270 performers and artists in a ceremony billed as a celebration of humanity and the unifying power of sport.\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1743, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We knew you would be brilliant, but you were magic,\\\" Paris 2024 organising chief Tony Estanguet told athletes.\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1827, \"end\": 1841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You made us happy, you made us feel alive - the world needed this moment so much.\\\"\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Al Jazeera English:\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 1968, \"entities\": []}]}"